grants arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe grants farm aid farm aid grants provide support for bringing the arts into the classroom grants are used to subsidize class trips to course related performances and exhibitions artist visits to classes and studios and materials for course projects and productions farm aid grants are available to faculty for undergraduate and graduate courses in any department or school instructors may apply for up to $1500 per course please note farm aid funding is limited to one grant per course per quarter farm aid grant timeline applications for the 2011 12 academic year are now accepted on a rolling basis throughout the school year please expect a two week period for grant review before receiving a response funds are limited so apply early a quarter in advance if possible please read the instructions thoroughly before applying instructions apply now workshop with taiko master kiyonari tosha questions call the sica office at 650 736 4087 or email sica stanford edu back home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
